Description: Fragment of a green stone scarab, pierced lengthwise, with elytra marked and base inscribed with the end of the name Wahibra.
Excavator/field collector: Excavated by: Sir William Matthew Flinders Petrie
Curator's comments: One of "two scarabs of green jasper... name Psametik I. (or Uah-ab-ra)" mentioned by W.M.F. Petrie, Tanis ii, Nebesheh and Defenneh, p. 73 § 70, p. 111, pl. xli, 56 (the other one, pl. xli, 58, is London, BM, EA 18534).
Bibliographic references: Petrie 1888 / Tanis. Part II. Nebesheh (Am) and Defenneh (Tahpanhes) (p. 73 § 70, p. 111, pl. xli, 56)
Leclère and Spencer 2014 / Tell Dafana Reconsidered: The Archaeology of an Egyptian Frontier Town (p.66, p.181, pl.23)
